headline: TI increases dividend 4% to $1.42 per share, marking 22 consecutive years of increases
summary: Texas Instruments Incorporated (TI) (Nasdaq: TXN) today said it will raise its quarterly cash dividend 4%, from $1.36 per share to $1.42, or $5.68 annualized. The higher dividend will be payable November 12, 2025, to stockholders of record on October 31, 2025, contingent upon formal declaration by the board of directors at its regular meeting in October.
